Hey guys. I'll be talking about Numstore (aka smartfiles) next week on Tuesday (May 26th) at the same time as our book club but 1 day earlier (16:30 UTC) for ~1 hour (including questions). No homework for this one, and no need to be a database guru - I'm certainly not :)

The rough Agenda will be 
- Use cases for array based databases (and why there aren't any in industry yet)
- The core operations on an array: (insert, remove, write, and read)
- The Rope+Tree (a rope-like variant of the B+Tree commonly used in databases),
- Architecture of a fault tolerant single file database (and how it could scale), buffer pools, WAL's, concurrency
- Lots more

The project is in C, but you don't need to know C
